### Basic environment variable in URL
GET {{base_url}}/api/users

### Multiple environment variables in URL
GET {{protocol}}://{{host}}:{{port}}/api/users

### Environment variables in query parameters
GET https://example.com/api/users?token={{api_token}}&version={{api_version}}

### Environment variables in headers
GET https://example.com/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
X-API-Version: {{api_version}}
Custom-Header: {{custom_header_value}}

### Environment variables in request body
POST https://example.com/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "apiKey": "{{api_key}}",
  "settings": {
    "theme": "{{theme}}",
    "notifications": {{notifications_enabled}}
  }
}

### Environment variable with default value
GET {{api_url:https://default-api.example.com}}/v1/resources
